with him for years

00:01:33.770 --> 00:01:38.660 align:middle line:84%
until he sold it to, I
believe, Francis I in 1508.

00:01:38.660 --> 00:01:41.540 align:middle line:84%
So it's a great
painting by the man

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:44.360 align:middle line:84%
I consider to be the greatest
genius who ever lived.

00:01:44.360 --> 00:01:48.380 align:middle line:90%
And it has undefinable powers.

00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:50.180 align:middle line:90%
It's a mystery.

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:55.024 align:middle line:90%
And it's a painting about women.

00:01:55.024 --> 00:01:57.440 align:middle line:84%
And Leonardo didn't really
know how to connect with women,

00:01:57.440 --> 00:01:59.481 align:middle line:84%
I think, on a really
emotional or physical level,

00:01:59.481 --> 00:02:03.008 align:middle line:84%
but yet he captured the beauty
of women through that piece.

00:02:03.008 --> 00:02:06.494 align:middle line:90%
