Russia had tested

00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:08.470 align:middle line:84%
the largest nuclear
weapon in history

00:04:08.470 --> 00:04:15.160 align:middle line:84%
at 50 megatons on
October 31, 1961.

00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:20.290 align:middle line:10%
On October 22, 1962,
President John F. Kennedy

00:04:20.290 --> 00:04:23.260 align:middle line:10%
alarmed the world media
that the Soviet Union

00:04:23.260 --> 00:04:27.250 align:middle line:10%
was building secret missile
bases in Cuba, dangerously

00:04:27.250 --> 00:04:31.000 align:middle line:10%
close to the state of Florida
and within striking distance

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:33.790 align:middle line:10%
of most major American cities.

00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:37.180 align:middle line:84%
This set off national panic
that the United States

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:40.420 align:middle line:84%
was at the brink of a
nuclear war with Russia.

00:04:40.420 --> 00:04:43.790 align:middle line:84%
It was clear Russia
was ready to go to war.

00:04:43.790 --> 00:04:46.570 align:middle line:84%
The United States
was very tense.

00:04:46.570 --> 00:04:50.200 align:middle line:84%
President Kennedy skillfully
avoided the nuclear conflict

00:04:50.200 --> 00:04:53.440 align:middle line:84%
with Russia despite
pressure from US generals

00:04:53.440 --> 00:04:55.300 align:middle line:90%
who wanted a war.

00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:59.440 align:middle line:10%
On November 21,
1962, Russia agreed

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:03.760 align:middle line:10%
to withdraw its nuclear bombers
and 40,000 Russian troops

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:05.380 align:middle line:10%
from Cuba.

00:05:05.380 --> 00:05:09.280 align:middle line:84%
At this time, First lady Jackie
Kennedy had arranged with

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:13.480 align:middle line:84%
the French government's cultural
minister AndrÃ© Malraux to have

00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:16.960 align:middle line:84%
the "Mona Lisa" visit the
United States of America.

00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:21.010 align:middle line:84%
To do this, the "Mona Lisa"
would be transported from Paris

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:25.720 align:middle line:84%
to New York by ocean
liner in December 1962,

00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:30.070 align:middle line:84%
only days after the Russian
nuclear climate was cooling.

00:05:30.070 --> 00:05:33.160 align:middle line:84%
Mrs. Kennedy was obsessed
with the "Mona Lisa."

00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:36.250 align:middle line:84%
and yet she would risk
moving it across the Atlantic

00:05:36.250 --> 00:05:38.560 align:middle line:84%
with a chance of a
possible flare up

00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:41.500 align:middle line:84%
amongst the danger
of Russian vessels.

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:44.050 align:middle line:84%
Did Jackie Kennedy
use the "Mona Lisa"

00:05:44.050 --> 00:05:46.600 align:middle line:84%
to tame the tension
in the Atlantic,

00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:49.330 align:middle line:84%
knowing the Russians wouldn't
dare strike while the "Mona

00:05:49.330 --> 00:05:52.780 align:middle line:84%
Lisa" was being transported,
or was her cause

00:05:52.780 --> 00:05:55.300 align:middle line:84%
a gamble for the
people's morale?

00:05:55.300 --> 00:05:58.330 align:middle line:84%
Regardless, "Mona
Lisa" prevailed

00:05:58.330 --> 00:06:01.780 align:middle line:84%
on what seems her first
global peace mission.

00:06:01.780 --> 00:06:06.250 align:middle line:10%
On January 8, 1963,
the "Mona Lisa" exhibit

00:06:06.250 --> 00:06:08.740 align:middle line:10%
opening at the
National Gallery of Art

00:06:08.740 --> 00:06:13.300 align:middle line:10%
was in concert with the opening
session of the 88th Congress.

00:06:13.300 --> 00:06:16.390 align:middle line:84%
"Mona Lisa" was in attendance
of the entire House

00:06:16.390 --> 00:06:20.500 align:middle line:84%
of Representatives, the Senate,
the Kennedy administration,

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:22.450 align:middle line:90%
and the Supreme Court.

00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:25.060 align:middle line:84%
A Washington
newspaper commented,

00:06:25.060 --> 00:06:28.300 align:middle line:84%
"Seldom in the history of
the United States of America

00:06:28.300 --> 00:06:30.130 align:middle line:84%
has the ruling
class been present

00:06:30.130 --> 00:06:33.505 align:middle line:90%
in such overwhelming numbers."

00:06:33.505 --> 00:06:37.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Mr. Minister, we in the
