00:08:15.580 --> 00:08:18.970 align:middle line:90%
happy female that I really like.

00:08:18.970 --> 00:08:22.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Leonardo da Vinci
was born on April 15,

00:08:22.240 --> 00:08:28.690 align:middle line:84%
1452 in a small village called
Vinci near Florence, Italy.

00:08:28.690 --> 00:08:32.590 align:middle line:84%
His father was Piero
da Vinci and his mother

00:08:32.590 --> 00:08:35.230 align:middle line:90%
a peasant girl named Catarina.

00:08:35.230 --> 00:08:39.669 align:middle line:84%
Leonardo da Vinci was not
only a master painter.

00:08:39.669 --> 00:08:46.600 align:middle line:84%
He was a scientist, an engineer,
inventor, biologist, musician,

00:08:46.600 --> 00:08:49.120 align:middle line:90%
writer, and mathematician.

00:08:49.120 --> 00:08:51.310 align:middle line:10%
While many scholars
do not believe

00:08:51.310 --> 00:08:54.310 align:middle line:10%
he encrypted his art
with hidden messages,

00:08:54.310 --> 00:08:56.920 align:middle line:10%
the "Mona Lisa's"
dimensions reveal

00:08:56.920 --> 00:08:59.680 align:middle line:10%
the truth once and for all.

00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:04.940 align:middle line:10%
Mona Lisa is 77
by 53 centimeters.

00:09:04.940 --> 00:09:15.300 align:middle line:84%
If we divide 77 centimeters
by 53, we get 1.4528301887.

00:09:15.300 --> 00:09:20.920 align:middle line:84%
We can clearly see that
the first digits, 1.452,

00:09:20.920 --> 00:09:23.290 align:middle line:84%
is the year that
Leonardo da Vinci was

00:09:23.290 --> 00:09:26.620 align:middle line:84%
born, proving that
the masterpiece is

00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:29.200 align:middle line:90%
coded with deeper meaning.

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:34.120 align:middle line:84%
What else is hidden
in the Mona Lisa?

00:09:34.120 --> 00:09:39.100 align:middle line:10%
>> The issue of divine
providence is challenged

00:09:39.100 --> 00:09:42.670 align:middle line:10%
by the early explorers
of astronomy.

00:09:42.670 --> 00:09:44.860 align:middle line:84%
Providence means that
the church actually

00:09:44.860 --> 00:09:48.520 align:middle line:84%
believed that all of the
bishops and the popes

00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:53.830 align:middle line:84%
were receiving their all
knowingness, their omniscience

00:09:53.830 --> 00:09:54.670 align:middle line:90%
from God.

00:09:54.670 --> 00:09:58.050 align:middle line:84%
And they were God's
authority on Earth.

00:09:58.050 --> 00:10:01.720 align:middle line:84%
In the first and second
councils of Nicaea,

00:10:01.720 --> 00:10:06.490 align:middle line:84%
the idea was that providence was
present in the decision making

00:10:06.490 --> 00:10:10.610 align:middle line:84%
process to isolate the four
gospels, Matthew, Mark,

00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:11.410 align:middle line:90%
Luke, and John.

00:10:11.410 --> 00:10:13.090 align:middle line:84%
And all of the other
manuscripts that

00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:17.050 align:middle line:84%
were submitted in the
council were rejected by God,

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:19.540 align:middle line:84%
because God's providence
was present in the council.

00:10:19.540 --> 00:10:22.270 align:middle line:84%
In fact, most Christians
believe this today.

00:10:22.270 --> 00:10:25.090 align:middle line:84%
But I believe, having
studied da Vinci,

00:10:25.090 --> 00:10:28.930 align:middle line:84%
that he was a rebel, that
he took the position, as I

00:10:28.930 --> 00:10:33.010 align:middle line:84%
do, of the anti-Nicaean fathers,
the fathers of the church that

00:10:33.010 --> 00:10:37.210 align:middle line:84%
were against the decision making
process to reject literally

00:10:37.210 --> 00:10:40.240 align:middle line:84%
hundreds and hundreds of
manuscripts that may have been

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:42.710 align:middle line:90%
the true words of Jesus Christ.

00:10:42.710 --> 00:10:44.850 align:middle line:10%
But later, the church
actually believed

00:10:44.850 --> 00:10:48.730 align:middle line:10%
that, even scientifically,
it possessed this providence

00:10:48.730 --> 00:10:54.040 align:middle line:10%
that God's divine providence was
present in the all-knowingness

00:10:54.040 --> 00:10:56.050 align:middle line:10%
of science in the universe.

00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:57.700 align:middle line:10%
The early church
adhered to the idea

00:10:57.700 --> 00:11:01.060 align:middle line:10%
of Ptolemy's geocentric
view of the universe

00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:03.640 align:middle line:10%
that the Earth was the
center of the universe

00:11:03.640 --> 00:11:07.770 align:middle line:10%
and that the sun revolved
around the Earth.

00:11:07.770 --> 00:11:10.650 align:middle line:10%
I discovered, from
studying da Vinci's notes,

00:11:10.650 --> 00:11:13.950 align:middle line:10%
that da Vinci may have
been the first person

00:11:13.950 --> 00:11:18.630 align:middle line:10%
to actually secretly disclose
that the Earth was revolving

00:11:18.630 --> 00:11:24.150 align:middle line:10%
around the sun, which
is the heliocentric view

00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:25.630 align:middle line:10%
that later evolves.

00:11:25.630 --> 00:11:29.880 align:middle line:84%
Now Copernicus, the
Polish astronomer,

00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:31.230 align:middle line:90%
actually believed this.

00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:34.110 align:middle line:84%
In fact, he comes just a
little bit after Vinci.

00:11:34.110 --> 00:11:36.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're both
alive at the same time.

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.500 align:middle line:90%
They're contemporaries.

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:40.470 align:middle line:84%
It's possible they might
have even exchanged ideas.

00:11:40.470 --> 00:11:43.770 align:middle line:84%
But Copernicus waits until
he's nearing his death

00:11:43.770 --> 00:11:48.210 align:middle line:84%
to disclose the truth that
actually the Earth is not

00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:50.490 align:middle line:84%
the center of the universe
and the church was wrong.

00:11:50.490 --> 00:11:52.110 align:middle line:90%
And there was no Providence.

00:11:52.110 --> 00:11:56.330 align:middle line:84%
God was not present in its
all-knowingness in the bishops

00:11:56.330 --> 00:12:00.930 align:middle line:84%
and the pope in the
scientific authority of God

00:12:00.930 --> 00:12:02.070 align:middle line:90%
and the universe.

00:12:02.070 --> 00:12:06.480 align:middle line:84%
In fact, what happens
later is Galileo

00:12:06.480 --> 00:12:09.060 align:middle line:84%
adopts the same
ideas of Copernicus

00:12:09.060 --> 00:12:13.860 align:middle line:84%
that the Earth is actually
revolving around the sun.

00:12:13.860 --> 00:12:17.670 align:middle line:84%
Once per year, the Earth
makes a solar orbit.

00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:20.010 align:middle line:84%
And later, of course,
as astronomy evolved,

00:12:20.010 --> 00:12:22.500 align:middle line:84%
we realized that
all the nine planets

00:12:22.500 --> 00:12:25.920 align:middle line:84%
are revolving around the
sun as a solar system.

00:12:25.920 --> 00:12:28.650 align:middle line:84%
And the solar system
is oscillating

00:12:28.650 --> 00:12:32.560 align:middle line:84%
around the galaxy every
250 million years.

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:34.950 align:middle line:84%
So there are orbits within
orbits within orbits.

00:12:34.950 --> 00:12:36.629 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
you have Hubble

00:12:36.629 --> 00:12:38.670 align:middle line:84%
has now discovered there
